The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
Persons must introduce themselves to the Consulate for a visa application prior to their conversation; the costs will be reduced in this way.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will change in the United States Embassy and in the consulates.
In the new procedure, most applicants have to introduce themselves to the Visit Application Services (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their consultation at the Consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the applicant's biometric data, which shall be verified by the consulate prior to the discussion.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total costs for the management of the visa are reduced because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the date agreement, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is issued.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counter value of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who wish to extend their visa only do not have to have a conversation in the consulate; they only have to imagine the next ASC where they present their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants requiring a second date for the consultation at the consulate remain less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the $26 service supplement.
